2 hours ago, editor99 said:

I'm currently trying to identify the mod(s) that cause this crash, but I have no idea what it could be. 

  1. The mod KSPAPIExtensions throws an exception at the very beginning of your load because it can't access  the file
    • C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Kerbal Space Program\GameData\NetherdyneAerospace\CivilianManagement\Plugins\KSPAPIExtensions.dll
    • You should check if NetherdyneAerospace is installed correctly. 
  2. You are also running the game from Steam and Steam notoriously can have missing files from time to time. 
    • In  you Steam  Library  right click on Kerbal Space Program and select Properties
    • Go to the Local Files section  on the left menu of the Properties window.
    • Select the Verify integrity of the games files  
    • When this is complete any missing files from you base install will be replaced. 

If this fixes the issue for you you might consider copying your C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Kerbal Space Program\  directory  to another location on your hard drive and launching the KSP64.exe  from the new location.  This prevents the disappearing Steam files problem.
